title: Drawing, "End Table", early 20th century
medium: Graphite on tracing paper, ruled border in graphite
markings: Stamp in black ink at lower right: DONALD DESKEY/630 FIFTH AVENUE/ NEW YORK CITY
inscribed: Inscribed in graphite at lower left: #4577; lower right in graphite: SCALE 1"=1'0"/8458 [circled]; lower right in red color pencil: P; dimensions in graphite throughout.
description: Perspective, plan, and elevation drawing for bleached mahogany end table. Rectangular table has two shelves, supported on both sides by wide leg/slab of wood with rounded top edge. Width of shelves on both sides extend beyond side legs.
